<item>
            <title>[LU-13471] LNet: discovery can glitch</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13471</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When discovery is initiated from a MR node to another MR peer, we will send the GET message from source NID-A, but the PUSH message from source NID-B. The PUSH will not be recognize because the peer doesn&apos;t have any record of NID-B yet and will drop the push. This will result in asymmetric information. The MR node will have a record for the peer NIDs, but the peer will not have a record of the node&apos;s NIDs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
